message: "If you use this computational assay in your research, please cite it using the metadata below."
title: "Computational Diagnostic Assay for ASL Discourse Exclusion Patterns"
authors:
  - family-names: "Markson"
    given-names: "Phinn"
    orcid: "0000-0002-9169-6095"
version: 1.0.0
date-released: "2026-06-18"
url: "https://github.com/phinnphace/decoder"
abstract: > This DOI provides the source code for a computational diagnostic assay designed to identify, structure, and log known failure patterns of vision models based upon their underlying training datasets.
The assay surfaces correlational phraseologies paired with their anatomical counterparts, revealing failure clusters regardless of whether vision model (VM) authors disclose their training data (proprietary claims, incomplete documentation, etc.).
 This diagnostic instrument brings training data transparency to light through user-reported failure modes.
keywords:
  - American Sign Language
  - Discourse Analysis
